slot_description: Are insurance coverages being explained?
example_value: So we're going to take care of your car damage because you have collision coverage for that and it covers all the repairs with or without any fault or deductible. And then we will also cover medical expenses for you and your passengers as well because you have medical payment coverage in your policy.

Describe the motion of the referents vehicle.
Description of the speed of the referent.   This may include specific values, like 45 mph, as well as less specific terms like they were going really fast.

possible_slot_values: ['caller party cited', 'other party cited', 'no party cited', 'multiple parties cited', 'unsure', 'no ticket']
slot_description: Did any of the parties receive a ticket or some other citation from the police?
The police report number.
Were there skid marks at the scene of the accident?
Was an ambulance used?  Note that words like paramedic or EMT are also indicative of ambulance.
What body part(s) were injured?
What was the nature of the injury?
The points of impact on the referent vehicle.  Note that several values may be provided for any given point of impact.
Location of the accident or loss.  Includes specific locations, for example, highway or street names, but also includes vague descriptions of locations, like in front of my moms house.
Number of passengers in the referent vehicle.   Number of passengers should not include the driver.

Were any witnesses present?  Even if the text indicates that there were no witnesses, or caller is not sure if there were any witnesses, the text should still be marked as witness, and the value no or unknown marked accordingly.
Were children involved in the accident?
Were the airbags in the referent's vehicle deployed?
Was the referent's vehicle towed from the scene?
Were any pedestrians involved in the accident?
Approximate date of the loss.  Includes specific dates, as well vague descriptions of days, like two days ago.
Approximate time of the loss.  Includes specific times of day, as well vague descriptions of time, like after work.
For any information regarding the specifics of a vehicle, including the make, model, model year, etc of the vehicle.
Where was the driver headed to?   This can be a specific location, like an address, or it can be more vague statement like I was heading to the supermarket.
Where did the driver start?   This can be a specific location, like an address, or it can be more vague statement like I was coming home from work.
Mileage on a vehicle.
Was the referent driving for a ride share service, like Uber, Lyft, etc?
The weather and visibility conditions.  Select all that apply.
Were there any obstructions to the view, for example objects in the roadway, etc?
What is the condition of the roadway?   Select all values that apply.

possible_slot_values: ['stop sign', 'yield sign', 'green light', 'yellow light', 'red light', 'other', 'unsure', 'no signal or sign']
slot_description: Description of the traffic signal, including traffic lights and stop signs.   Select the most descriptive value, for example, while a flashing red light is technically also a red light, only select one.
Description of the lanes.
How many lanes on the road.   Be sure to use context in determining the number.  For example, if the text says 2 lanes in each direction then the value should be 4.
Description of the traffic condition, for example, whether the traffic was light or heavy.
The speed limit.
Description of the traffic flow, for example, the direction of traffic.
Description of parking lot.
